HEADWORD: Paronomasia
<hw>Par`o*no*ma"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to form a word by a slight change; <grk>para`</grk>
beside + <?/ to name, fr. <grk>'o`noma</grk> a name.]</ety>
<fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A play upon words; a figure by which the same
word is used in different senses, or words similar in sound are set in
opposition to each other, so as to give antithetical force to the
sentence; punning.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

